Read five space-separated values in this order:

1. int
2. long long
3. char
4. float
5. double

Print each value on a new line in the same order as the input.

Input Format
One line containing:
int long long char float double

Output Format
Print each value on a separate line.

Constraints
-2147483648 ≤ int ≤ 2147483647
-2^63 ≤ long long ≤ 2^63 - 1
char: valid ASCII character
float and double follow IEEE 754 standards

Example Input:
3 12345678912345 a 334.23 14049.30493

Example Output:
3
12345678912345
a
334.23
14049.3

Note:
Read the values using their respective data types and print them exactly in the same order, each on a new line.


#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int main()
{
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);cout.tie(0);

  int a;
  long long b;
  char c;
  float d;
  double e;
  cin>>a>>b>>c>>d>>e;
  cout<<a<<endl;
  cout<<b<<endl;
  cout<<c<<endl;
  cout<<d<<endl;
  cout<<e<<endl;


}
